    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#boardman1966"/>, pp. <citedRange>153-155</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/>, pp. 233-235, n. <citedRange>3</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>000500</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015a"/>, pp. <citedRange>65, 68</citedRange> </bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#antonini2016"/>, p. <citedRange>45</citedRange></bibl> and 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/> <citedRange>2017.638</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-60850"><name nymRef="#Ἀπονίκας">Ἀ<unclear>π</unclear>ονίκας</name></persName> 
                    <w lemma="γράφω">ἔγ<unclear>ρ</unclear><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">απσε</supplied></w>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem>Ἀ<unclear>π</unclear>ονίκας</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#cdl1970">ἀπὸ νίκας <note>Masson's reading</note></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">      
                <p>Aponikas a inscrit.</p>
          
                <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>Aponikas inscribed.</p>
                </div>

                <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>Aponikas ha iscritto.</p>
                </div>

                <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The letters may be either Cyrenaean or Theran, so the graffito might have been scratched at either places (see also at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr000300</ref>).</p>                    
                    <p>The reading <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀπονίκας</foreign> is now conforted by another occurrence at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr122400</ref>.</p>
                <p>Antonini's idea that the penultimate preserved letter, instead of being a gamma, might be a chi with trident-shape is not sustainable (see photograph).</p>
                <p/>
            </div>
       </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>أبونيكاس نقش أو كتب</p>
         </div></body>
    </text>
